// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p13/pass.test — P13 basic `#line` recognition per
// `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` §2.4 + the contract topic table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/preprocessor-seam.contract.md`.
//
// Topic per the table: "`#line` round-trip golden (see above)".
// This single-fixture variant exercises P13's basic round-trip:
// input `#line 100 "synth.v"` followed by ordinary NSL on the next
// line — the output token stream contains a canonical `#line 100
// "synth.v"` directive (variant 2) and subsequent tokens report
// `synth.v:100:…` for their virtual coordinates.
//
// Verified through the `<phys-loc>` and `<virt-loc>` columns in
// `-emit=tokens` output per
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/nslc-emit-tokens.contract.md`:
//   <phys-loc> := <path>:<line>:<col>:<offset>   (physical, the temp file)
//   <virt-loc> := <path>:<line>:<col>            (virtual, post-#line)
//
// For the first NSL token after `#line 100 "synth.v"`:
//   <phys-loc> = %t.nsl:2:1:NN     (line 2 of the temp file)
//   <virt-loc> = synth.v:100:1     (post-#line virtual)
//
// Tasks.md T049 + spec.md US2 acceptance #8.
//
// **RED state**: the existing Phase-3 lexer recognizes `#line` as
// `tk_line_directive` (per the lexer fix in commit ecfee46) but
// does NOT update the SourceManager's virtual-line table — that's
// preprocessor work (FR-020). So `<virt-loc>` against the unchanged
// tree still reports the physical coordinates. Phase-4 wires the
// virtual update via `SourceManager::addLineDirective()`.

// RUN: echo '#line 100 "synth.v"' >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'reg z;'              >> %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// First, the canonical #line directive crosses the seam (P12 + P13
// — `#line` is one of the two artifacts permitted to cross). The
// directive's spelling is preserved exactly (variant 2: number +
// string-literal).
// CHECK: tk_line_directive

// Then the post-#line tokens report virtual coordinates synth.v:100.
// `tk_reg` lands on physical line 2 of the temp file; its virtual
// loc is `synth.v:100`.
// CHECK: tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:2:1:{{[0-9]+}}{{[ \t]+}}synth.v:100:1
// CHECK: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}z{{[ \t]+}}{{[^:]+}}:2:5:{{[0-9]+}}{{[ \t]+}}synth.v:100:5
